FBIS4-23475 "drafr109_d_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique Government Allegedly Giving Indian Guru Land Government Allegedly Giving Indian Guru Land MB0606121694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1100 GMT 6 Jun 94 MB0606121694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] An alleged agreement in terms of which the Mozambican Government will give an Indian spiritual leader, Maharishi Mahesh Yogi, nearly a quarter of the country is causing controversy. Government sources say plans are being laid to amend the stipulations of the agreement. The agreement was allegedly signed by the finance minister with the agreement of President Joaquim Chissano. Latest speculation is that 20 million hectares of land is being made available to the maharishi for his Heaven on Earth Development Company. The maharishi is the former spiritual leader of the Beatles.
